\subsubsection{Weapon Breaks and Drops}

An unmodified Strike Check of 99 indicates that the attacker may have
broken their weapon; similarly, a Strike Check of 100 indicates a
potential weapon drop. In either case, the attacker must make a 3 \x MD
check to avoid the misfortune. The attacker also automatically misses
their target.

A dropped weapon usually falls in the attacker's hex, and may be
picked up later, but a broken weapon cannot be used. When a Break or
Drop is indicated for an attack where it is not possible, the attack
misses, and the GM may require that the attacker's next action be a
pass action to recover.

