     action  next  Pulse.  If  the  modified  result  is   4
     through   7,   the   attacker   has    been    Disarmed
     per the attack of the same name (see 16 .     5).      1      f
     the  niodified  result  is  8  or  above,  the   attack
     has  been  Parried  to  the   extent   that   the   at-
     tacker   has   become   Disarmed   and    the    target
     may   execute   a    Melee    attack    instantaneously
     against  him   without   need   to   perform   an   at-
     tack  action.  This  is   called   a   Riposte.   A
     Riposte  may  never  itself  be  Parried  and   may
     occur  as  many  times  during  a  PuLse   as   the
     evading  target  was  Melee  attacked,   A   target
     may  even  Parry  attacks   which   do   not   come
     through  his  Melee   Zone   (e.g.,   from   behind
     him).  An  unarmed  figure  may  Parry  if  he   is
     Ranked in Unarmed Combat (see 21.0).
