and   any   damage   points   not   absorbed    are    in-
fl . icted    on    the    figure    and    subtracted     from
either    Fatigue     or     Endurance.     Any     damage
points  actually  inflicted  on  the   figure   (not   ab-
sorbed     by     armor)     are     termed      Effective
Damage.

     There   are   three   types    of    damage    possible
from   a   successful    strike,    depending    on    how
low   the   attacker   rolled   on    the    Strik@@.Check:
Damage     affecting      Fatigue;      affecting      En-
durance;     and     Grievous     Injury.     When     th6
