\item[Weight]   The   weight   of   the   weapon    in
pounds (or ounces, if so noted).
d1252 29
a1280 44
\item[Physical   Strength]   The   minimum    Physical
Strength-a figure  needs  to  wield  the  weapon
properly; a figure without the PS to  meet  this
minimum  does  one  less  point  of  damage  for
each  point  of  strength  he   is   below   the
minimum.  A  figure  may  ne\%,er  achieve   Rank
in a weapon he does not have the  PS  to  wield.

\item[Manual   Dexterity]   The   minimum    modif,,ed
Manual Dexterity a  figure  needs  to  maneu\,er
the  weapon  properly;  a  figure  without   the
MD  to  meet   this   minimum   has   the   Base
Chance of the weapon  lowered  by  5  for  everv
point he is below the mini,-num.  A  figure  mav
never achieve Rank  in  a  weapon  he  does  not
have the MD to maneuver.

\item[Base  Chance]  The  base   percentage   of   the
Weapon to score a successful hit on a figure.

\item[Damage   Modifier]   The   number    added    to
the DIO  die  roll  then  peforming  a  Damaee
Check; the modified  total  may  never  be  less
than 1.

\item[Range]  The  distance   (expressed   in   hexes)
which the weapon may be Fired.

\item[Class]  A  letter  representing  the   type   of
damage  done  by  the  weapon.  A  weapons  do
thrusting  damage.   B   weapons   do   slashing
damage.   C   weapons   do   crushing    damage.
Used for determining Grievous Injuries,

\item[Use] A letter representing the 1),pe(s)  of  at-
tack the weapon may  be  used  in.  R  indicates
Ranged  combat.  M   indicates   Melee   combat.
C  indicates  Close  combat.  A   'A,eapon   may
not be used in an attack type for  which  it  is
not rated.

\item[Cost]  The  cost,  in  Silver  Pennies,  to  pur-
chase  the  weapon.  At  the  cost  listed,   the
weapon is of normal quality.
