tempt  the  attack  anyway,  and  combat   begins.

     The   GM   draws   out    the    surroundings,
places the  characters'  miniatures  on  the  Dis-
play,  and  then  places  the  monsters'  figures.
He  determines  the   characters'   Fatigue   loss
(due  to  their  long  march),   and   adjudicates
the  monster's  Fatigue  status.  He  allows   the
characters to prepare a  weapon,  if  thev  wish,
because of thealertness ofeaelewing.

